SIMPLE: hundreder
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hundreder
<hw>Hun"dred*er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>An
inhabitant or freeholder of a hundred.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>A person competent to serve on a
jury, in an action for land in the hundred to which he
belongs.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>One who has the jurisdiction of a hundred; and
sometimes, a bailiff of a hundred.</def> <rj><au>Blount.
Cowell.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hundredfold</ent>⟦br⟧
